DRDGold, Interwaste Holdings May Move: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-24T05:32:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-23/drdgold-interwaste-holdings-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index gained
347.24, or 1.1 percent, to 31,215.55 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.  Basil Read Holdings Ltd. (BSR)  : The construction and
engineering company releases annual earnings. The company said
yesterday net income declined as much as 10 percent. The shares
climbed 35 cents, or 3.4 percent, to 10.75 rand.  DRDGold Ltd. (DRD SJ): The mining company’s Blyvooruitzicht
mine near Carletonville will close for a day of mourning
following the  death of eight workers  in a bus accident on March
18, according to both the  National Union of Mineworkers  and
management. The stock rose 11 cents, or 3.5 percent, to 3.30
rand.  Interwaste Holdings Ltd. (IWE)  : The industrial waste-
management group said it expects to report a loss per share of
between 3.50 cents and 4.10 cents for the year through December.
The 2009 loss will probably be adjusted to 2.80 cents and 3.30
cents a share, according to a trading update late yesterday. It
didn’t provide a reason. The shares declined 1 cent, or 2.1
percent, to 47 cents.  Poynting Holdings Ltd. (POY)  : The telecommunications
equipment maker releases fiscal first-half earnings. The company
on March 3 said it posted a loss in the six months through
December. The stock was unchanged at 21 cents.  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) gained 1.6 percent to $25.35.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) rose 2.7 percent to $46.45. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) advanced 1.9 percent to $75.72.  DRDGold
Ltd. (DRD)   jumped 5.8 percent to $4.95. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) gained 2.9 percent to $17. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) advanced 8.3 percent to $13.49. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) rose 1 percent to $28.57. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US) fell
1.2 percent to $4.90. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) gained 0.9 percent to
$54.46.  To contact the reporter on this story:
